getDataValues

public Object getDataValues(String utype)
                     throws SedInconsistentException,
                            SedNoDataException
Gets the values of the specified utype. If no data exists then a SedNoDataException is thrown. If the utype is not supported a SedInconsistentException is thrown. For points where the utype is not set a default value is used; for doubles its NaN for ints its -9999.

Parameters:
utype - String
Returns:
either double[] or int[] depending on the data. The arrays will be cast to an Object.
Throws:
SedInconsistentException, - SedNoDataException

setDataInfo

public void setDataInfo(Field field,
                        String utype)
                 throws SedInconsistentException,
                        SedNoDataException
Sets the parameter info of the specified utype. The specfied field will replace all information on each point except for the value. If no data exists for the specified utype on a particular point the point will be ignored. If there are no points to set, a SedNoDataException is thrown. If the utype is not supported a SedInconsistentException is thrown.

Parameters:
field - Field
utype - String

Sets the parameter info of the specified utype. The specfied field will replace all information on each point except for the value. If no data exists for the specified utype on a particular point the point will be ignored. If there are no point to set, a SedNoDataException is thrown. If the library cannot find a parameter associated with the specified utype a SedInconsistentException will be thrown.
